{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 17:01:11.147484", "event": "llm_end", "text": "I have submitted the final solution with the following details:\n- Anomaly detected: Yes\n- Faulty devices: web_server_0, web_server_1, web_server_2, web_server_3\n- Root cause: sender_application_delay\n\nRationale: HTTP TTFB spikes occur only when accessing the Apache web servers directly, while L2/L3 connectivity, OSPF routing, and DNS resolution are healthy. TCP connect times are low, pointing to server-side application delays (likely reverse DNS or synchronous per-request lookups) before first byte is sent. The load balancer path remains consistently fast, further isolating the issue to the web servers.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2232, "output_tokens": 138, "total_tokens": 2370, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 2048}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
